Finally, let's find the intersection of all three Cartesian products:

A x B ∩ (A x A) ∩ (B x B) = {(2, 2)}

Comparing the results, we can see that:

(A ∩ B) x (A ∩ B) = {(2, 2)} = A x B ∩ (A x A) ∩ (B x B)

Thus, we have proved that (A ∩ B) x (A ∩ B) = A x B ∩ (A x A) ∩ (B x B).
